Name: Test
Short description: Largo is a specially designed gated sanctuary perfect for those perceptive people looking to host conferences, retreats, and even weddings in a unique and creative space. Largo is located just an hour?s drive from Miami International Airport, is easy to access, and offers many amenities. Being able to host around 100 guests the event space is divided into a dock area, a beach area, as well as indoor space. The rental of Largo for destination events includes exclusive use of the entire estate; private beach; infinity pool; 3 bedroom main lodge & 6 guest bungalows (comfortably sleeping up to 15 single guests or 30 as couples); daily housekeeping and groundskeeper. To ensure privacy, admittance to Largo is by reservation or appointment only.

Name: 1111 Lincoln Road
Short description:
Indeed 1111 is a unique and spectacular venue. Designed by internationally renowned, Pritzker Prize winning architects Herzog & de Meuron, 1111 Lincoln Road is a modernist masterpiece which elevates the senses and enhances the moment. The panoramic ocean, city and bay views enjoyed from our vantage point are sheer perfection, and offer an unparalleled glimpse of Miami that could happen no place else in the world. 1111 Lincoln Road has been recognized by one of the top 25 most architecturally significant buildings in the state of Florida. The soaring 34 foot ceilings, the expansive views and the lights of the city are mesmerizing. There's nothing else like it, and it's truly the quintessential Miami experience.

Name: Alfred Dupont Building
Short description:
The Historic Alfred I. DuPont Building's mezzanine level began its utilization as a special events venue in 2001, with elegant historical detail and understatedly opulent decor. The venue, a former bank headquarters, complete with teller windows and two bank vaults, quickly became a highly sought-after event venue for an enterprising clientele looking for Miami style accented with New York glamour.

Name: The Temple House
Short description:
The Temple House is a spectacular and exceptional event space. Designed by one of the most famous Art Deco architects in history, this remarkable building has been fully renovated and is available for private events. With approximately 16,000 square feet this year-round air-conditioned breathtaking facility features a Grand Room with 25 foot ceilings, a beautiful mezzanine, catering space, and more. Name: Vizcaya Museum and Gardens
Short description:
We?ve coined the phrase ?Very Vizcaya? to describe an experience or situation that captures the complexity and contradiction of this landmark estate. Vizcaya is beautiful and serene. But it is also a place of intellectual stimulation, compelling us to consider the relationships between native and foreign, old and new, and natural and designed. The curiosity that brought you here today suggests you?re probably already forming your own opinion of why Vizcaya is special and worthy of our efforts to preserve it. Vizcaya has been described as ?the finest private house ever built in America,? ?a jewel among Miami?s skyscrapers and subdivisions,? and ?some Noah?s Ark of decorative arts,? its exteriors offering the ?manic tranquility of the great European folly gardens.? Most of us who know Vizcaya well embrace this place for both its serious significance and its eccentric charm.

Name: The Woman's Club of Coconut Grove
Wynwood Walls + Wynwood Private Room
Short description:
The Wynwood Walls was conceived by the renowned community revitalizer and placemaker, the late Tony Goldman in 2009. He was looking for something big to transform the warehouse district of Wynwood, and he arrived at a simple idea: “Wynwood’s large stock of warehouse buildings, all with no windows, would be my giant canvases to bring to them the greatest street art ever seen in one place.” Starting with the 25th–26th Street complex of six separate buildings, his goal was to create a center where people could gravitate to and explore, and to develop the area’s pedestrian potential.

We have day tours, and night tours, both for individuals or private. Name: Story Nightclub
Short description:
Since opening in 2012, Story has become an unparalleled, high-energy lightlife experience located in the heart of Miami Beach. Story is the brainchild  of nightlife mogul David Grutman and Miami MArketing Group, the company behind the world famous LIV at Fountainbleau. The expansive 27,000sqf. space  is equipped with a State-of -the-Art infinite hybrid sound system in addition to its concert style lighting and visuals which are truly unmatched by any other nightclub in Miami Beach.
